HEADWORD: Edulcorator
<hw>E*dul"co*ra`tor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A contrivance
used to supply small quantities of sweetened liquid, water, etc., to any
mixture, or to test tubes, etc.; a dropping bottle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Edulious</ent>⟦br⟧
